The paper deals with the problem of extracting an automaton from a trained recurrent neural network, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of machine learning and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of abstract interpretation and exact learning, which are techniques commonly used in the field of computer security (cs.CR) and control theory (cs.SY), respectively.
